race.comment: Former Victorian REZONE (11) couldn't have been more impressive saluting over this track and trip when having the first run for the new stable and will have taken a bunch of confidence from that victory. Sure to be right there when the judge calls a halt. ABSOLUTE SUNSHINE (6) is another former Mexican having his first run for the new barn but should find this assignment easier than what he faced down south. Respect any market confidence. LUTON HOO (7) has won two from three here and gets the reliable Vandyke/Maloney combination. Capable of sharp improvement. Feel like SAN JOSE BOY (12) can be a big improver second up.
